  <span id="freeText4992515378763035942" style="display:none">As I read further into the Brother Cadfael series, each installment becomes more engaging and the characters more interesting. While tHe stories are set in the twelfth century, they have a timeless import, relevance, and interest. While the series centers around Brother Cadfael, this novel centers around the characters of the individual story of which he is just one. In this installment, the abbey is conducting their annual fair when murder, intrigue, and danger are thrust upon several of the fair goers and local villagers. Intrigues play out and the lives of many hang in the balance. </span>
